                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client who has been prescribed disulfiram (Antabuse). Which statement by the client indicates to the nurse the need for further teaching about this medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nClients who are taking disulfiram must be taught that substances containing alcohol can trigger an adverse reaction. Sources of hidden alcohol include foods (soups, sauces, vinegars), medicine (cold medicine), mouthwashes, and skin preparations (alcohol rubs, aftershave lotions).\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Psychiatric: Alcohol Deterrents\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Addictions\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Addiction, Patient Education\nStrategies: Negative Event Query, Strategic Words, Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, need for further teaching. These words indicate a negative event query and ask you to select an option that is an incorrect statement. Focus on the subject and recall that disulfiram is used for clients who have alcoholism and that any form of alcohol needs to be avoided with this medication.",
                        "id": "3d9fae1fb8fc46e9aa4dbf473ad355fd",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "08d66a7e1632442790e3f6e6a94c5309",
                                "content": "If there is a history of hyperthyroidism"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d32aa7f5a6d04276bedc378c98339b0b",
                                "content": "When the last full meal was consumed"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6b5cbf17d2c04aefaf91b7b227e26951",
                                "content": "If there is a history of diabetes insipidus"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
